      • GeoCoordinate

        public GeoCoordinate(double... coordinateData)
        Create coordinate with given latitude, longitude in degrees and altitude in meter

        NOTE: Will only use the first three entries in coordinateData, will fail less than three entries

        Parameters:
        coordinateData - Coordinate data to copy array or variable argument list data from. Ordering: latitude, longitude, altitude.

      • GeoCoordinate

        public GeoCoordinate(int latitudeE6,
             int longitudeE6,
             double altitude)
        Create coordinate with given latitude, longitude in degrees and multiplied by 10^6 and altitude in meter

        NOTE: Will only use the first three entries in coordinateData, will fail less than three entries

        Parameters:
        latitudeE6 - The latitude in degrees and multiplied by 10^6
        longitudeE6 - The longitude in degrees and multiplied by 10^6
        altitude - The altitude in meter
